'''{{Conjecture|Harold Theopolis}} "Harry" Osborn''' is a social media influencer and the only son of [[Norman Osborn/Norman Osborn-Mentored Spider-Man|Norman Osborn]]. Being saved from the muggers by [[Spider-Man/Norman Osborn-Mentored Spider-Man|Spider-Man]], Osborn soon found out that Spider-Man was working together with his father, so Norman recruited him to assist Spider-Man in his absence. Excited to work with Spider-Man on saving [[New York City]], Osborn became close friends with Peter Parker, and despite initial tensions with [[Nico Minoru/Norman Osborn-Mentored Spider-Man|Nico Minoru]], the two became friends as well. Osborn encouraged Parker to follow his own way as a hero and when he decided to quit [[Oscorp]] internship, Osborn founded [[W.E.B.]] to support other young geniuses and help them improve the world without a fear of being exploited.

==Biography==
{{MD|Harold Osborn (Earth-TRN1450)}}
===Son of a Billionaire===
====Media Influencer====
{{Quote|Hey, the first few years are a blast. But once you realize there's no one around to talk to, since all your old friends are busy at school and all your new friends are either using you for clout or are just spam bots, the shine starts to wear off the whole experience.|Harry Osborn to [[Spider-Man/Norman Osborn-Mentored Spider-Man|Peter Parker]]|The Unicorn Unleashed!}}
Harry Osborn was born to [[Norman Osborn/Norman Osborn-Mentored Spider-Man|Norman]] and [[Emily Osborn]], although his mother would not be around for long.{{Ref|YFNSM106}} As his father was the CEO of [[Oscorp]] and one of the richest people in [[New York City]], Harry lived his life in great affluence. Norman decided to homeschool Harry, hiring the best teachers the money could buy, and although Harry did enjoy it at first, it soon started to feel isolating.
[[File:Luna Snow & Harry Osborn.png|{{AltFloat}}|Osborn meets [[Luna Snow]]]]
As a teenager, Harry started became a famous social media influencer, with his follower count exceeding two million. Having access to Norman's wealth, Harry attended a lot of high-profile events around the globe, had a trip to [[Pisa]], and even had a photo with [[Luna Snow]]. However, Harry longed to have a real friend in his life, as most people were around him only for his money or for clout. Growing up, Harry was a fan of [[Steve Rogers/Norman Osborn-Mentored Spider-Man|Captain America]], something that would not change even after he was branded an international criminal.{{Ref|YFNSM105}}

===Meeting Spider-Man===
====[[Rescue of Harry Osborn|Saved by Spider-Man]]====
{{Quote|How can I thank you? I mean, like, I tried to tell those guys, I don't really carry cash but, I mean, do you have {{WPS|Venmo}}?"<br>"Hey, don't worry about it, uh, citizen?"<br>"Uh... It's Harry.|Harry Osborn and [[Spider-Man/Norman Osborn-Mentored Spider-Man|Spider-Man]]|Amazing Fantasy}}
''To be added''

====Meeting Peter Parker====
{{Quote|Ah, it's always so freaky getting off on this floor. I feel so out of place."<br>"Hey, if this is the place you're supposed to be, then you're not out of place. Right?|[[Spider-Man/Norman Osborn-Mentored Spider-Man|Peter Parker]] and Harry Osborn|Hitting the Big Time}}
''To be added''

===Dude at the Desk===
====Discovering Spider-Man's Identity====
{{Quote|Holy crap! You're Spider-Man.|Harry Osborn to [[Spider-Man/Norman Osborn-Mentored Spider-Man|Peter Parker]]|Hitting the Big Time}}
