==Trivia==
*In the comics, Harry Osborn was a friend of [[Peter Parker]], but after finding out that Parker was Spider-Man, he inherited his [[Green Goblin|father]]'s mantle of '''Green Goblin'''. Osborn would later marry [[Liz Allan]] and have a child named [[Normie Osborn|Normie]].
*Harry Osborn appeared on a variant cover of the first issue of ''[[Your Friendly Neighborhood Spider-Man (comic)|Your Friendly Neighborhood Spider-Man]]'' despite not appearing in that issue.
*Unlike most versions where he is portrayed as a rich yet unpopular teenager who is classmates with Peter Parker, this version of Harry Osborn is a homeschooled, rich and popular social media influencer.
**Harry Osborn has yet to become best friends with Peter Parker until Peter accidentally reveals his secret identity in front of him.
*Harry Osborn being appointed as Spider-Man's "dude-at-the-desk" is a reference to [[Ned Leeds]]' role as Spider-Man's "guy-in-the-chair" in the live-action movies.

